      <h4>Adding updated mods</h4>
      <details class="tapShow">
        <summary>Manual Installation</summary>
        <p>Just simply follow step 2 under the <b>First time installing mods</b>. Which is simply installing the mods from the <code>necessary.zip</code>/<code>optional.zip</code> file and dragging it to the <code>mods</code> file.</p>
        <p>It is recommended that you <b>delete</b> everything from the mods folder. There are some instances where the zip file has some updated mods!</p>
        <br>
        <p>Before intalling the new mod zip file. Double the check the <a href="/mod_versions/">mod logs</a> if there are any changes.</p>
        <br>
        <p>Simply install the zip file below (either one that has been officially updated),</p>
        <br>
        <p>
        <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-4rGxNzsFt3c1bKWI0uNN-HxiRPZwxin/view?usp=sharing" class="zip-button">mods.zip</a>
        </p>
        <br>
        <p>Open the zip file and drag it to the <code>mods</code> file. It will pop-up that there will be some files that might be duplicated. Simply click <b>Skip these files</b> (the second option).</p>
        <img src="/images/install-mods-images/1.1-exmaple-of-many-files-added.png" alt="">
        <p>And that is it!</p>
      </details>

      <details class="tapShow">
        <summary>With CurseForge</summary>
        <p>WIP</p>
      </details>

